claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: A CONSORT flow diagram showing enrollment, randomization, allocation, and follow-up of participants over two influenza seasons (2018–2019 and 2019–2020) into four vaccine groups in Year 1 (ccIIV4, RIV, Fluzone IIV4, Fluarix IIV4) and re-randomization in Year 2. does not support the claim because the diagram provides participant flow and group sizes but contains no information on hemagglutinin microgram content per strain for any vaccine.
